            "currentCldrName": "Moon Viewing Ceremony",
            "description": "<p>Moon Viewing Ceremonies (called <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tsukimi\">Tsukimi</a> in Japan) are held each year in <a title=\"🍂 Fall / Autumn\" href=\"/fall-autumn/\">autumn</a> to celebrate the <a title=\"🌕 Full Moon Symbol\" href=\"/full-moon/\">full moon</a> and <a title=\"🌒 Waxing Crescent Moon Symbol\" href=\"/waxing-crescent-moon/\">waxing moon</a> in Japan.</p>\n<p>This symbol shows Japanese pampas grass and <a title=\"🍡 Dango\" href=\"/dango/\">dango</a> (sweet dessert food) which are used in the ceremony, as well as the moon in the background.</p>\n",
